==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Regress
<hw>Re"gress</hw> <pr>(r?"gr?s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>regressus</ets>, fr. <ets>regredi</ets>, <ets>regressus</ets>. See
<er>Regrede</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of passing back;
passage back; return; retrogression. ⟦ldquo⟧The progress or
<xex>regress</xex> of man⟦rdquo⟧.</def> <rj><au>F.
Harrison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The power or liberty of passing back.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Regress</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Regress
<hw>Re*gress"</hw> <pr>(r?*gr?s")</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Regressed</conjf>
